# Market Scout environment.
#
# These run live with NO keys, no login, and no card -- nothing below required:
# - Nominatim (OpenStreetMap) for address -> coordinates
# - Overpass (OpenStreetMap) for nearby businesses
# - Mangrove Reviews (open review dataset) for real public review text where
#   it has coverage
# The app produces real, worldwide results out of the box on these alone.
#
# Everything below is OPTIONAL and only adds richer data. Copy this file to
# ".env.local" and fill in whatever you have.

# --- Reddit (local discussion) [OPTIONAL] ---------------------------------
# NOTE: Reddit's keyless public search now returns 403, so real Reddit data
# requires a free "script" app from https://www.reddit.com/prefs/apps
# (client id + secret below). Without it, the Reddit signal is simply skipped.
REDDIT_CLIENT_ID=
REDDIT_CLIENT_SECRET=
REDDIT_USER_AGENT=market-scout/0.1 by u/yourusername

# --- AI-written synthesis [OPTIONAL] ----------------------------------------
# Leave both blank to use the built-in template synthesis, which is still
# built from real data (real business names, real area facts) -- just phrased
# by a template instead of an LLM.
#
# Gemini (Google AI Studio) is genuinely free, no credit card required: sign
# in with a Google account and generate a key at https://aistudio.google.com
# /apikey. Preferred automatically when set. Free-tier limits (Gemini 2.5
# Flash, as of writing): ~10 requests/minute, 250 requests/day -- plenty for
# personal use, and the app's own rate limiter (below) already caps analyze
# requests well under that.
GEMINI_API_KEY=
# MARKET_SCOUT_GOOGLE_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash

# Anthropic (Claude) -- paid, no free tier. Used only if GEMINI_API_KEY and
# FREELLMAPI_API_KEY are not set.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# MARKET_SCOUT_AI_MODEL=claude-sonnet-5

# FreeLLMAPI (github.com/tashfeenahmed/freellmapi) -- self-hosted local proxy
# that aggregates free tiers from Groq, Google AI, and others behind one
# OpenAI-compatible endpoint. Preferred over Gemini/Anthropic when set. Run
# the proxy locally first (its default port is 3001), then paste the unified
# "freellmapi-..." key it gives you below. NEVER commit a real key here --
# put it in .env.local only, which is gitignored.
FREELLMAPI_API_KEY=
# FREELLMAPI_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3001/v1
# FREELLMAPI_MODEL=auto

# --- Optional tuning -------------------------------------------------------
# Force fully offline sample data everywhere (no network calls at all):
# MARKET_SCOUT_FORCE_MOCK=1
# MARKET_SCOUT_RADIUS_METERS=2500
# MARKET_SCOUT_MAX_PLACES=40
# MARKET_SCOUT_MAX_REDDIT=25

# --- Bot control / DoS protection [ALWAYS ON, no config needed] -----------
# Two keyless layers protect /api/analyze and /api/geocode/suggest:
#  1. Same-origin check (lib/bot-control.ts) -- rejects any request that
#     didn't come from this app's own page (checked via the browser's Fetch
#     Metadata / Origin headers), which blocks scripts and bots hitting the
#     API directly with a 403.
#  2. Per-IP rate limiting below.
# Together these stop the overwhelming majority of scripted abuse and DoS
# traffic for free, and also protect this app's shared identity on Nominatim/
# Overpass/Mangrove/Wikipedia from getting rate-limited or banned by a flood
# of requests funneled through us.

# --- Rate limiting (POST /api/analyze) [OPTIONAL] --------------------------
# Keyless, in-memory, per-IP fixed-window limiter -- no external service.
# Max requests per window per client IP (default 10 -- kept tight since this
# route fans out to several external services per call):
# MARKET_SCOUT_RATE_LIMIT=10
# Window length in milliseconds (default 60000 = 1 minute):
# MARKET_SCOUT_RATE_WINDOW_MS=60000
# Set MARKET_SCOUT_RATE_LIMIT=0 to disable rate limiting (local dev/testing).
